<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id8ee55945-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s290o–3"><num value="290o–3">§ 290o–3.</num><heading> Federal Reserve Banks as depositories</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any Federal Reserve Bank which is requested to do so by the Bank may act as its depository, or as its fiscal agent, and the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System shall exercise general supervision over the carrying out of these functions.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id8ee55946-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/104/208/dA/tI/s101/c/tVII/s705">Pub. L. 104–208, div. A, title I, § 101(c) [title VII, § 705]</ref>, <date date="1996-09-30">Sept. 30, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/3009-121">110 Stat. 3009–121</ref>, 3009–179.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
